Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
11:29 a.m.  Defendant waives her right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant is bound over to Circuit Court Branch 3 for trial.
ARRAIGNMENT - 
Information filed. Copy served on defense counsel.
Not guilty plea(s) entered.  Jury calendar.
Offer deadline:  5/13/22, 8:30 a.m.
Minutes.
Further proceedings scheduled for May 13, 2022 at 08:30 am.

2:01 pm - Prosecuting attorney Angelina R Scarpelli in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Amber Marie Wachowski appeared by video.  Attorney Dominique McQueen appeared by video for Amber Marie Wachowski. Defendant demands a preliminary hearing. Preliminary hearing is set for 04-07-22 at 10:30 a.m.
Preliminary hearing on April 7, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Order to report to TRPD for photo and prints

BAIL HEARING - 
Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crime of possess schedule I or II narcotic, possess drug paraphernalia and felony bail jumping.  The matter is continued for initial appearance on 03-21-22 at 1:30 p.m.  Bail is set at $2,500.00 recognizance bond with the conditions that he report to the Two Rivers Police Department for fingerprints, photographs and identifying information within 48 hours or, if incarcerated, within 72 hours of release and defendant must maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol and drugs.  Bail furnished and defendant is released from custody.
Minutes.
